Date: 2002-11-28

Title: Integrable Structures in String Field Theory

Authors: L. Bonora, A.S. Sorin

Comments: 11 pages; v.2

Solvable and Integrable SystemsJournal-ref: Phys.Lett. B553 (2003) 317-324

We give a simple proof that the Neumann coefficients of surface states inWitten's SFT satisfy the Hirota equations for dispersionless KP hierarchy. In asimilar way we show that the Neumann coefficients for the three string vertexin the same theory obey the Hirota equations of the dispersionless Toda Latticehierarchy. We conjecture that the full (dispersive) Toda Lattice hierachy and,even more attractively a two--matrix model, may underlie open SFT.